ots\nIn the Bronx\nLeft to them by\nJohn Masterson Burke\nShould be sold for\nWhatever they will bring\nTo help relieve\nThe housing congestion.\nThe funds to help carry on\nThe work of the Institution\nWhich restores to health\n5,000 convalescents a year\nTaken from the hospitals\nOf New York City.\nOn about 30 of these lots\nThere is a pig farm\nAnd we have tried\nTo move the pigs\nBefore the sale,\nBut you see\nPigs is Pigs\nAnd every time\nWe try to move\nThese prolific pigs\nNew pigs keep coming\nSo there we are.\nBut these lots\nHave got to be sold anyway\nNo matter what they bring\nAnd as they are\nWithin a few blocks\nOf a Subway station\nAt Gun Hill Road\nAnd at Burke Avenue,\nOn Boston Post Road\nAnd other leading\nAvenues and Streets\nSuitable for homes\nIn a rapidly growing\nSection of the Bronx\nWhich in a few years\nWill be built up with\nStores and apartment houses\nAnd as lot values are now\nAt the bottom\nAnd in a short time\nAre bound to rise rapidly\nIn value\nThey should make a\nGood speculation\nOr a good investment.\nGo up and see the pigs\nAt the same time,\nLook at the lots.\nRemember! Mrs. Goelet had her cows\ngrazing at 19th Street and Broadway\nnot many years ago!\nGo to the absolute auction sale of 1400 lots\nWITHIN THE 5c FARE ZONE\nOn Boston Post Road, Burke Ave., Gunhill Road and Adjoining Sts.\nbetween 204th and 212th Streets\nAt the Hotel Astor,\n&*H\nJUNE 22nd, 23rd and 24th\n80% can remain on mortgage\nGO EXAMINE THE PROPERTY TODAY\nTake Bronx Park Subway to Burke Avenue or Gunhill Road\nStation. Property it a few minutes' walk east of Station.\nSend for bookmap at once\nJ. CLARENCE DAVIES, 149th st 3rd Ave.\nJOSEPH P. DAY, 67 Liberty Street\nAgents and Avctioneers.\nBROOK17VN REAL ESTATE I LKOOKLYN REAL ESTATE\nMake sure of your\nfuture home at once\nP0S5ESS10N IMMEDIATELY (gKif AA POSSESSION OF BALANCE\nof one apartment %D*J**\\J\\* October 1, 1920\nCo-op?rative Plan\n\nCcrner De Ka!b Ave., Brooklyn\nThere are a few of the choice